# Walkthrough — Data Freshness, AI Model, Brief Flow, Doc Upload

## Prerequisites Before Testing

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Restart your dev server** (`Ctrl+C` then `npm run dev`). The Prisma client needs to regenerate for the new schema changes, and the file was locked by the running process.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Re-save your AI key.** Go to Settings → AI Keys → delete the existing Gemini key → add a new one with model `gemini-2.5-flash` (or `gemini-2.0-flash`). The old `gemini-1.5-pro` model no longer exists.

---

## Changes Made

### Fix 1 — Data Freshness (No More 15-20s Delays)

**Root cause**: Next.js Server Components cache database queries. After a mutation (create group, accept invite, etc.), the old cached data was served until the cache expired.

**What changed**:

#### `export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic'` added to 5 pages:
- [dashboard/page.tsx](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/dashboard/page.tsx#L1) — Active/Previous Groups list
- [dashboard/group/[id]/page.tsx](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/dashboard/group/[id]/page.tsx#L1) — Group Dashboard
- [dashboard/group/[id]/tasks/page.tsx](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/dashboard/group/[id]/tasks/page.tsx#L1) — Task Board
- [join/[code]/page.tsx](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/join/[code]/page.tsx#L1) — Join page

This tells Next.js: "never cache this page — always run the server component fresh."

#### `revalidatePath()` added to 10 mutation API routes:
| Route | Paths Revalidated |
|---|---|
| [POST /api/groups](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/api/groups/route.ts) | `/dashboard` |
| [POST /api/groups/join](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/api/groups/join/route.ts) | `/dashboard`, `/dashboard/group/[id]` |
| [POST /api/invitations](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/api/invitations/route.ts) | `/dashboard`, `/dashboard/group/[id]` |
| [PATCH /api/invitations/[id]](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/api/invitations/[id]/route.ts) | `/dashboard`, `/dashboard/group/[id]` |
| [POST /api/groups/[id]/leave](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/api/groups/[id]/leave/route.ts) | `/dashboard`, `/dashboard/group/[id]` |
| [DELETE /api/groups/[id]/previous](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/api/groups/[id]/previous/route.ts) | `/dashboard` |
| [POST /api/briefs](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/api/briefs/route.ts) | `/dashboard/group/[id]` |
| [POST /api/ai/assign-tasks](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/api/ai/assign-tasks/route.ts) | `/dashboard/group/[id]`, tasks page, `/dashboard` |
| [PATCH /api/profile](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/api/profile/route.ts) | `/dashboard` |
| [PATCH /api/tasks/[id]](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/api/tasks/[id]/route.ts) | tasks page, group page |

**How to verify**:
1. Open two browser tabs: one as user A, one as user B (incognito or different Clerk account).
2. User A creates a group → User B sends a join request via invite code.
3. **Without refreshing**, check User A's group dashboard → the pending request should appear within 1-2 seconds.
4. User A accepts the request → User B's dashboard should show the group immediately.

