### Fix 3 — Brief + AI Failure Loop

**Problem**: If the AI failed, the brief was saved. Retrying said "brief already exists" (409).

**What changed**:
- [briefs/route.ts](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/api/briefs/route.ts#L119-L155) — If a DRAFT brief exists, **update** it instead of rejecting with 409. Only lock after ANALYSED.
- [ai/assign-tasks/route.ts](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/api/ai/assign-tasks/route.ts#L208-L226) — If brief status is ANALYSED, delete existing tasks and reset to DRAFT before re-running.
- [brief/page.tsx](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/dashboard/group/[id]/brief/page.tsx) — Added `router.refresh()` after submit.

**How to verify**:
1. Submit a brief → let AI run.
2. If AI fails (intentionally use a bad key to test): the error message shows but clicking "Submit Brief & Assign Tasks" again will work — no more "brief already exists" error.

